description: Indian authorities have identified fifteen local Kashmiri overground workers (OGWs) as suspects in facilitating the recent Pahalgam terror attack. Electronic surveillance revealed their potential involvement in logistics and arms procurement from Pakistan. Three prime suspects are detained, with police seeking two others.
title: 15 local cadres helped Pahalgam attackers: Probe

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat asserted that while non-violence is integral to Indian culture, taking action against a hostile neighbor like Pakistan, especially after the Pahalgam terror killings, is a 'dharma'.
title: Action against hostile neighbour is dharma: Mohan Bhagwat

description: Aligarh jail celebrated a remarkable 100% success rate as five inmates cleared their UPMSP board exams. Yogesh Pandey and Dharmendra Kumar passed the high school exams, while Netrapal Singh, Vishal Kumar, and Rajesh Kumar cleared the intermediate examinations. Prison officials expressed joy, highlighting the positive impact of education within the jail walls, offering a glimmer of hope for the inmates.
title: Aligarh jail inmates clear UP Board exams with 100% success

description: A powerful explosion ripped through a firecracker factory near Deoband, Saharanpur, resulting in the tragic deaths of three workers and critical injuries to at least six others. Police arrested the factory owner and his two sons for allegedly exceeding permissible production limits.
title: Blasts in 2 firecracker units claim 6 lives

description: Citing past security breaches like the Kargil War and the 26/11 attack, the Centre has issued a strong advisory to media outlets, urging restraint in reporting defence operations. The advisory aims to prevent real-time coverage and source-based reporting that could compromise national security, especially amidst escalating tensions following the Pahalgam attack.
title: Centre bars live media coverage of defence operations

description: Ramesh Jarkiholi, a BJP MLA and former minister, faces charges filed by Karnataka CID in a Bengaluru court for allegedly defrauding Karnataka Cooperative Apex Bank and associated district cooperative banks of Rs 439 crore. The chargesheet alleges violations of loan conditions related to Soubhagya Laxmi Sugars Ltd.
title: CID charges Jarkiholi with 439 crore 'bank fraud'

description: The Resistance Front (TRF), a Lashkar-e-Taiba proxy, retracted its claim of responsibility for the Pahalgam terror attack, attributing it to a cyber intrusion. This denial follows international acceptance of India's stance that LeT, backed by Pakistan, was behind the attack. Security sources dismiss the retraction as a ludicrous damage control attempt by Pakistan's ISI to evade accountability.
title: Fearing hit-back, LeT proxy does U-turn, says no hand in Pahalgam attack

description: The Enforcement Directorate seized Rohan Harmalkar's house after finding property documents worth Rs 600 crore. Harmalkar, an independent candidate in 2022, identified unattended properties, often with deceased owners or those living abroad. He then allegedly used impersonation and forged documents to sell these properties to clients, mainly from Delhi-NCR and Haryana, at below-market prices.
title: Goa property fraud: Many buyers from NCR

description: In a historic move, Ayodhya's Hanuman Garhi temple's chief priest, Mahant Prem Das, will break a 300-year-old tradition by visiting the Ram temple. This unprecedented event, permitted by religious bodies, will see Mahant Das leave Hanuman Garhi on April 30th in a grand procession featuring elephants, camels, and Naga Sadhus.
title: Hanuman Garhi temple's chief priest to break 300-yr tradition for Ram Temple visit

description: The Karnataka High Court has issued notices to the state government and KEA regarding a PIL alleging that CET exam centers in Bidar, Shivamogga, and Dharwad forced candidates to remove their Janivara (sacred thread). The petitioner, Akhila Karnataka Brahmana Mahasabha, claims students were mistreated during the math exam and barred from entering if they refused.
title: HC notice to Karnataka govt over forced removal of sacred thread

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, during a virtual event distributing employment letters to over 51,000 new recruits, emphasized the crucial role of government employees in bolstering India's internal security. His address, following the Pahalgam attack and amid concerns about Pakistan's destabilizing efforts, urged the new recruits to dedicate themselves to strengthening the nation's economy, infrastructure, and the lives of workers.
title: It's your duty to bolster internal security, govt staffers told

description: Despite a recent terrorist attack that killed 26 tourists, Pahalgam is gradually welcoming visitors again. Tourists are returning, drawn by the area's beauty and the absence of travel restrictions. Locals and security personnel are supportive, and businesses are offering discounts. While Baisaran meadow remains closed, other attractions are open, signaling a slow return to normalcy for the picturesque resort town.
title: J&K: Post-attack, tourists start to reappear in Pahalgam

description: In Aligarh, a 27-year-old man has been sentenced to life imprisonment for the 2023 murder of his 55-year-old father-in-law, stemming from a property dispute. The victim's 11-year-old son's testimony, placing the accused with his father before his death, proved crucial in the conviction. While the son-in-law was convicted, his associates were acquitted due to insufficient evidence.
title: On 11-yr-old's testimony, man gets life term for killing father-in-law

description: Pahalgam police are re-verifying pony guides and locals. This follows the Baisaran meadow attack on April 22. Initial tourist statements and social media videos prompted the action. Twenty pony handlers are being questioned. Hundreds of pony owners were called for verification. Police are also verifying shawl sellers, Maggi vendors, and villagers near Baisaran. Even local police are recording statements.
title: Pahalgam massacre: Ponywallahs quizzed by cops, being 're-verified'

description: The UN Security Council condemned the Pahalgam attack in Jammu & Kashmir, but Pakistan, supported by China, worked to dilute the statement's phrasing. Unlike the Pulwama attack condemnation, which urged cooperation with the Indian government, the Pahalgam statement only mentioned "all relevant authorities." This change followed tough negotiations, with Pakistan likely seeking to avoid giving India leverage in investigations.
title: Pakistan, backed by China, dilutes UNSC statement

description: UAE President Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan and Iranian counterpart Masoud Pezeshkian called PM Modi, condemning the Pahalgam attack. Gulf nations are working to ease tensions between India and Pakistan. Leaders emphasized rejecting terrorism and ensuring justice for the perpetrators, with India briefing diplomats on Pakistan's alleged role in cross-border terrorism.
title: UAE & Iran presidents call PM Modi, slam Pahalgam attack

description: A mazaar, estimated to be at least 50 years old and situated within the Govt Doon Medical College and Hospital in Dehradun, was demolished late Friday night. The demolition was carried out by civic agency teams and district administration officials, supported by a strong police presence.
title: 'Unauthorised' mazaar razed in Doon hospital

description: Tensions flared in Jaipur's walled city after BJP MLA Balmukundacharya and supporters allegedly engaged in provocative sloganeering near Jama Masjid during a protest against the Pahalgam massacre. An FIR has been filed against the MLA for allegedly hurting religious sentiments and inciting violence. CCTV footage shows the group pasting posters and raising anti-Pakistan slogans near the mosque, sparking widespread protests.
title: FIR against BJP MLA for 'provocative' rant outside Rajasthan mosque

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, security forces demolished Shahzada Bano's home after identifying her son, Adil Hussain Thoker, as a key suspect. Despite the family's claim of no contact since 2018, Adil's parents, brothers, and cousins are in custody, while his mother was briefly detained. Bano pleads for her son's surrender, hoping for peace amidst the turmoil.
title: J&K: Surrender so that we can live in peace, says terrorist's mom

description: Allahabad High Court has expressed serious concerns regarding Additional District Judge Amit Verma's inability to write judgments. The court directed that Verma, from Kanpur Nagar, undergo three months of training at the Judicial Training and Research Institute in Lucknow. This decision came after the judge dismissed an amendment application with a brief, unsubstantiated order.
title: Judge 'not competent' to write verdict, Allahabad HC sends him for training

description: India has announced the resumption of the Kailash Mansarovar Yatra in June 2025, after it was suspended in 2020 due to Covid-19. The pilgrimage will accommodate 750 pilgrims through Lipulekh Pass in Uttarakhand and Nathu La Pass in Sikkim. This move is part of broader efforts to rebuild ties with China, including discussions on trans-border river cooperation and people-centric services.
title: Mansarovar yatra to resume in June after five-year hiatus

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, Gujarat police launched a large-scale operation targeting illegal Bangladeshi residents, resulting in the arrest of 890 individuals in Ahmedabad and 134 in Surat. Four detainees are suspected of criminal links, including potential al-Qaida connections. Authorities are expediting deportation procedures and investigating the source of fraudulent documents used by the detainees.
title: Pahalgam fallout: 1,024 Bangladesh illegals arrested in Gujarat

description: The government is considering mandating anti-lock braking systems (ABS) for all two-wheelers exceeding 50cc to enhance safety and reduce accidents. Experts emphasize ABS and helmet use to protect vulnerable riders, who constitute a significant portion of road fatalities. Road safety experts also highlight the need for better transport planning and dedicated lanes to improve two-wheeler safety.
title: Safety first: Govt mulls mandatory ABS for all two-wheelers above 50cc
Saffron outfits targeting Kashmiris: Congress

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, police in Anantnag district, South Kashmir, have detained 175 suspects. Extensive search-and-cordon operations are underway with the collaboration of the Army and CRPF. Numerous raids were conducted, and security has been heightened across the district with additional checkpoints and intensified patrolling. J&K police also conducted searches at residences of terrorist associates in Srinagar.
title: 175 detained in anti-terror operations following Pahalgam terror attack

description: A sudden surge in the Jhelum river, allegedly due to India's unnotified water release from the Uri Dam, has triggered chaos in Pakistan-occupied Kashmir. This abrupt discharge led to a water emergency in Hattian Bala, forcing residents to evacuate. Pakistani authorities have condemned the action as a violation of the Indus Waters Treaty, escalating tensions between the two nations.
title: India’s sudden Jhelum water release sparks panic in PoK

description: A BJP delegation, headed by LAHDC chief Tashi Gyalson, engaged with Union Home Minister Amit Shah in Delhi, advocating for improvements in gazetted recruitment and updating Indian embassy websites to acknowledge Ladakh's UT status. They emphasized the importance of new districts for inclusive development and sought Shah's intervention to safeguard local youth's rights and restore budget allocations.
title: Ladakh council meets Amit Shah, wants India embassies update sites on UT

description: The Metropolitan Police are investigating a throat-slitting gesture by a Pakistani diplomat towards Indian protesters in London, who were demonstrating against a terror attack. The Pakistani high commission organized a counter-protest, escalating tensions with loud music and provocative signs. Amidst the chaos, arrests were made, and Indian protesters felt unfairly targeted by the police, alleging biased treatment.
title: Met Police probe Pak diplomat's throat-slitting gesture at Indian-origin protesters in UK

description: Amidst escalating tensions following the Pahalgam attack, Pakistan's PM Shehbaz Sharif has offered to join a neutral investigation, while also condemning India's accusations as baseless. Sharif asserted Pakistan's military readiness, warning against any misadventures, and cautioned India against blocking Pakistan's water share, threatening a strong response. The situation remains critical, with concerns of broader conflict looming large.
title: Pakistan ready for neutral probe into Pahalgam attack: Sharif

description: Pakistan violated the ceasefire along the Line of Control in Kashmir for the second consecutive night, prompting retaliation from the Indian Army. This follows the Pahalgam attack, where 26 civilians were killed by The Resistance Front, linked to Lashkar-e-Taiba.
title: Pakistan violates ceasefire along LoC, Indian Army retaliates
​Young Elon Musk told investor he's 'reincarnation' of Alexander the Great

description: The Kolkata Knight Riders and Punjab Kings match in the Indian Premier League 2025 got called off. Rain played spoilsport at Eden Gardens. Punjab Kings scored 201 for 4, with Arya and Prabhsimran hitting half-centuries. KKR's chase was cut short. Both teams shared a point. Punjab Kings are now fourth in the standings. Kolkata Knight Riders are seventh.
title: IPL 2025 Points Table: Latest standings after KKR vs PBKS match

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, the J&K government has deployed ministers to various states to address reports of threats and attacks against Kashmiris. These ministers are meeting with chief ministers and other officials to coordinate assistance and ensure the safety of Kashmiri students and business communities.
title: Omar’s ministers criss-cross states for safety of Kashmiris facing Pahalgam ‘backlash’

description: The IPL 2025 match between Punjab Kings and Kolkata Knight Riders ended in a no-result due to heavy rain. PBKS posted a competitive 201/4, powered by Prabhsimran Singh's explosive 83 and Priyansh Arya's rapid 69. KKR's bowlers, Vaibhav Arora and Andre Russell, managed to restrict PBKS in the final overs.
title: PBKS vs KKR becomes first IPL 2025 game to be called off
RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat's subtle endorsement to action against Pakistan

description: Rain interrupted the IPL match between Kolkata Knight Riders and Punjab Kings at Eden Gardens, halting KKR's chase of 202. If the match is washed out, both teams will share a point. Punjab Kings posted 201/4, powered by half-centuries from Priyansh Arya and Prabhsimran Singh, before Kolkata's bowlers fought back to restrict them in the final overs.
title: IPL 2025, KKR vs PBKS: What happens if rain washes out the match?

description: Prabhsimran Singh made history for Punjab Kings, becoming the first uncapped batter to surpass 1000 IPL runs. His explosive 83 against KKR, alongside Priyansh Arya's 69, propelled PBKS to a formidable 201/4. Prabhsimran's milestone and Arya's impressive debut season solidify Punjab's top order as they pursue their first IPL title.
title: New Record! Prabhsimran becomes first uncapped Punjab batter to ...

description: Pakistani health authorities are taking emergency measures to secure pharmaceutical supplies after trade ties with India were suspended. DRAP is exploring alternative sources in China, Russia, and Europe for raw materials and essential medicines. The PPMA has urged the government to exempt the pharmaceutical sector from the trade ban to avoid shortages of life-saving drugs.
title: Pakistan moves to secure medicines after India trade halt

description: Union minister Piyush Goyal asserted that incidents like the Pahalgam terror attack will persist unless all Indians prioritise patriotism and nationalism. He affirmed India's capability to respond strongly, emphasising that such acts won't deter the nation's spirit. Goyal expressed confidence in the swift resumption of Kashmir tourism and the continuation of the Amarnath Yatra, highlighting India's resolve to eliminate terrorism.
title: Patriotism must be 'param dharma' to defeat terrorism: Piyush Goyal

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, President Trump's remarks on India-Pakistan relations have sparked debate. His statement that they'll "figure it out" has been interpreted as either neutrality or tacit approval for India to act. While some see it as acknowledging historical religious tensions, others, like analyst Christine Fair, view it as a signal for India to address Pakistan's actions.
title: Playing neutral or free hand to India?: Teasing out Trump's post-Pahalgam comment

description: Delhi Capitals boast a strong spin attack with Kuldeep Yadav, Axar Patel and Vipraj Nigam, while RCB relies on Krunal Pandya and Suyash Sharma. RCB's spin coach praises Krunal's evolved action and Suyash's ability to turn the ball and deceive batters. Both teams are vying for the top spot in the points table, making their upcoming clash crucial.
title: How Krunal Pandya & Suyash Sharma are powering RCB's dream run
'No justification for ...': Iran President calls PM Modi, condemns Pahalgam attack

description: The bike gets LED headlamps, a tripper pod and a type-C USB charger. The 2025 Hunter 350 continues to be powered by a 349cc air-cooled J-series engine, producing 20.2hp of power and 27Nm of torque. It comes paired with a 5-speed gearbox, now enhanced with a slip-assist clutch.
title: 2025 Royal Enfield Hunter 350 launched in India at Rs 1.5L: What's new

description: The World Bank reports India lifted 171 million people out of extreme poverty between 2011-12 and 2022-23, reducing it to 2.3%. Using a $3.65/day poverty line, 378 million were lifted out of poverty. While significant progress occurred, challenges remain, including youth unemployment and gender disparities in employment, despite rising employment rates.
title: India lifted 171m people from extreme poverty in 11 years: World Bank

description: Shubman Gill, the Indian and Gujarat Titans batter, has dismissed rumours about his relationships, labeling them as "ridiculous." In an interview, the 25-year-old clarified he's been single for over three years, attributing the gossip to his demanding cricketing schedule. Gill emphasised his focus on his career, stating that his time on the road leaves little room for relationships.
title: Single? Dating? Gill sets the record straight on his relationship status

description: Amidst ongoing conflict, President Putin has expressed Russia's readiness for peace talks with Ukraine without preconditions, following remarks from Donald Trump. Simultaneously, Russia claims complete control over parts of the Kursk region, a statement Ukraine disputes, asserting continued defensive operations. Trump and Zelenskyy met at the Vatican, discussing potential ceasefire terms and expressing mutual interest in swift action towards peace.
title: Russia ready for Ukraine talks without preconditions, says Putin

description: Arjun Tendulkar is generating buzz, fueled by Yograj Singh's prediction of him becoming the "next Chris Gayle" if he prioritizes batting. Recent footage shows Arjun training with Zaheer Khan, further igniting excitement about his potential. With Mumbai Indians preparing for a crucial IPL match, Arjun might seize opportunities to prove himself as a rising star.
title: Arjun Tendulkar labelled 'tomorrow's legend' after Yograj's 'Gayle' remark

description: Donald Trump criticised Vladimir Putin for attacks on Ukrainian civilian areas, suggesting a change in approach through sanctions. This came after Trump's meeting with Volodymyr Zelenskyy in Rome, their first in-person encounter since February. Putin, meanwhile, expressed willingness for talks with Ukraine without preconditions during a meeting with a US envoy.
title: 'Maybe Putin doesn't want to stop war,' says Trump after meet with Zelenskyy

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath has strongly condemned the violence, assuring a firm response. He emphasized India's zero-tolerance policy towards terrorism, stating the nation is prepared to retaliate appropriately. Yogi expressed condolences to the victims' families, including Shubham Dwivedi's family from Kanpur, asserting that such acts are unacceptable and signal terrorism's decline.
title: 'Chhedoge toh chhodenge nahin': UP CM's warning after Pahalgam attack

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack that killed 26, Jammu and Kashmir Chief Minister Omar Abdullah has urged tourists to remain in the region, emphasizing that their departure would fulfill the attackers' goals. He acknowledged tourists' fears but assured them of support and instructed officials to assist those wishing to relocate.
title: 'If you leave now ... ': J&K CM's message for tourists after Pahalgam attack

description: Following the recent terror attack in Pahalgam, residents in the remote border villages of Poonch, Jammu and Kashmir, are preparing their underground bunkers, locally known as "Modi bunkers." These bunkers, built during Prime Minister Modi's tenure to protect civilians from cross-border shelling, are being restocked with essentials.
title: J&K villagers turn to 'Modi bunkers' as fears grow of India-Pak conflict

description: Ravi Shastri has lauded the emergence of promising young batsmen in the IPL. He specifically mentioned Ayush Mhatre, Vaibhav Suryavanshi, Priyansh Arya, and Prabhsimran Singh. Shastri highlighted their fearless approach and potential for international cricket. He advised caution regarding Suryavanshi, anticipating increased challenges for the young player. Shastri urged selectors to capitalise on current form when choosing players.
title: Shastri issues warning for Vaibhav Suryavanshi: 'There will be failures'

description: Mohan Bhagwat, the RSS chief, spoke about India's inherent non-violent nature. He stated that teaching a lesson becomes necessary when faced with evil. His comments follow the Pahalgam terrorist attack. Bhagwat emphasized the importance of unity within society. He added that strength must be visible when needed. He also mentioned that Hindus would never kill people after asking their religion.
title: 'Teaching lesson to hooligans a religion', says RSS chief
Top 5 news: Tensions rise along LoC after Pahalgam attack; and more

description: After a five-year hiatus due to the pandemic and border tensions, India and China will resume the Kailash Mansarovar Yatra in June 2025. The pilgrimage, significant for Hindus, Jains, and Buddhists, will proceed through Lipulekh Pass in Uttarakhand and Nathu La in Sikkim. This resumption signals a positive step towards mending bilateral relations following recent diplomatic discussions and troop withdrawals.
title: After 5 years, Kailash Mansarovar Yatra to resume in June this year

description: Russia confirmed North Korean soldiers aided in liberating the Kursk region from Ukrainian control, a claim made by Chief of Staff Valery Gerasimov to Vladimir Putin. Putin hailed the victory and the North Korean soldiers' "heroism." Zelenskyy met with Trump, discussing a ceasefire and lasting peace, hoping for a historic outcome.
title: In a first, Russia confirms North Korean soldiers in Ukraine

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, Pakistan's army chief, General Asim Munir, has reignited the two-nation theory, asserting the distinct nature of Muslims from Hindus across all facets of life. Munir emphasized Pakistan's resolve to defend itself, referencing actions taken by the Indian government after the attack. He also reiterated Pakistan's stance on Kashmir, referring to it as Pakistan's "jugular vein."
title: Pakistan army chief does it again, says 'Muslims distinct from Hindus'

description: Rohit Sharma, known for his mentorship, shared invaluable batting advice with LSG's Abdul Samad, emphasising personalised technique and adaptability to varying conditions. He highlighted the importance of mindset and leveraging individual talent, rather than imitation. This guidance comes ahead of a crucial IPL clash between Mumbai Indians and Lucknow Super Giants, both vying for playoff contention.
title: 'Tu mere jaisa nahin khel sakta ...': Rohit Sharma to young LSG batter
'Unjustified trade war': China hits out at 'extreme selfishness' of tariffs

description: Dr. Sriram Nene revealed Virat Kohli and Anushka Sharma's move to London. The couple sought to escape constant media attention in India. They desired a more private life for their family. Despite the move, Virat Kohli continues his cricket career. He recently achieved a record in the IPL. He scored his 26th half-century at M Chinnaswamy Stadium.
title: 'Virat Kohli, Anushka Sharma moved to London because ...'
Watch: When Pak defence minister blasted army in National Assembly
'Can a thief probe own theft?': BJP slams Pak PM's offer on Pahalgam

description: Content creator Misha Agrawal has tragically passed away, just two days shy of her 25th birthday, as confirmed by her family on Instagram. Known for her positive and relatable content, Misha's sudden death has sparked an outpouring of grief and heartfelt tributes from her devoted followers and the wider digital community.
title: Content Creator Misha Agrawal passes away two days ahead of her 25th birthday

description: Rahul Gandhi stated that the Bharat Jodo Yatra was initiated due to the Congress party feeling politically stifled, citing compromised media access and an oppressive political environment. He emphasized the need for a new kind of politician to address challenges like concentrated capital and modern media. Gandhi also highlighted the importance of education, healthcare, and democratic space.
title: 'Felt trapped & isolated': Rahul Gandhi on why he led Bharat Jodo Yatra

description: Jeff Bezos, despite his visionary leadership at Amazon, has faced numerous setbacks. Failures like the Fire Phone, Crucible, and Haven highlight the challenges of innovation and market disruption. Investments in dot-com era ventures such as Pets.com and Kozmo.com also resulted in significant losses, demonstrating the risks inherent in pioneering new business models.
title: How failed ventures, financial struggles paved way for Amazon's success

description: Ahead of their crucial match, Rohit Sharma's playful banter with Shardul Thakur during net practice has enlivened the Mumbai Indians camp. With both MI and LSG tied at 10 points, the upcoming clash at Wankhede is vital for playoff aspirations.
title: 'Kya re hero': Rohit Sharma's brutal roast goes viral - Watch

description: Karnataka's Chief Minister Siddaramaiah has expressed his opposition to war with Pakistan amidst escalating tensions following the Pahalgam terror attack, advocating for strengthened security measures in Kashmir. He also affirmed his government's commitment to deporting Pakistani nationals residing in Karnataka, as directed by the central government.
title: 'Not in favour of war': CM Siddaramaiah on India-Pak tension; BJP hits back

description: An underwater structure, Sycamore Knoll, sparks alien base theories. It disappeared from Google Earth but remains on fishing apps. UFO sightings are reported near the site. Military insiders share accounts of fast-moving underwater objects. Declassified footage shows a craft rising from the ocean. These events link to past UFO encounters off Southern California.
title: Possible underwater UFO base discovered off California coast

description: Rinku Singh acknowledges MS Dhoni's guidance for maintaining composure during high-pressure moments. He emphasises fitness and mental fortitude for IPL consistency. Singh learns from Andre Russell's power-hitting techniques. He believes that scoring 300 runs in an IPL match is achievable. Punjab previously chased down 262 runs. Singh highlights the strength of all teams this season.
title: Rinku Singh reveals Dhoni's advice behind his calm finishing role
Ukrainian troops forced out of Kursk, says Russia after Zelenskyy-Trump meet

description: Following a terror attack in Kashmir, Gujarat Police initiated a large-scale operation targeting illegal Bangladeshi residents. Hundreds were arrested across the state, with investigations revealing links to criminal activities, including suspected Al-Qaeda operatives. Authorities are intensifying operations, warning illegal residents to surrender, and focusing on exposing terror links and fake document networks.
title: Al-Qaeda operatives among 1,024 illegal Bangladeshis arrested in Gujarat

description: The Resistance Front (TRF) has retracted its claim of responsibility for the Pahalgam attack, attributing the initial message to a cyberattack orchestrated by India. The BJP mocked Pakistan's army, highlighting the terror outfit's fear due to India's stringent measures. Amid rising tensions, Pakistan offered a neutral probe into the attack, while Indian forces intensified anti-terror operations, detaining 175 suspects.
title: 'Humiliating retreat': BJP mocks Pak army after TRF denies role in Pahalgam

description: Chennai Super Kings suffered their seventh defeat in IPL 2025, losing to Sunrisers Hyderabad by five wickets at Chepauk, marking their fourth consecutive home loss. CSK's batting faltered, managing only 154 runs, with only Ayush Mhatre and Dewald Brevis showing resistance. Virender Sehwag criticised CSK's batting order and lack of responsibility, highlighting the absence of consistent scoring.
title: 'Jadeja's strike rate is useless': Sehwag slams CSK batting approach

description: Suresh Raina has criticised Chennai Super Kings after their recent loss to Sunrisers Hyderabad. Raina questioned the team's auction strategies and player performances. He highlighted MS Dhoni's continued dedication despite the team's struggles. Raina suggested that Dhoni's absence from key decision-making has hurt the team. Sunrisers Hyderabad defeated CSK, further jeopardising their playoff chances.
title: 'MS Dhoni aisa auction nahi kar sakta tha': Raina blasts CSK

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, intelligence agencies have identified 14 local terrorists active in Jammu and Kashmir, aged 20 to 40. These operatives, linked to Hizbul Mujahideen, LeT, and JeM, provide crucial support to Pakistani militants. Security forces have initiated joint operations in South Kashmir to disrupt terror support systems and prevent future attacks.
title: Pahalgam terror attack: Agencies name 14 active local terrorists in J&K
'Productive': Trump, Zelenskky hold brief talks before funeral of Pope Francis
Watch: Massive explosion rips through Iran port, 115 injured

description: An accident on the Delhi-Mumbai Expressway in Nuh district claimed the lives of seven sanitation workers, including six women, after a speeding van ran them over. Four others sustained critical injuries and were rushed to a Delhi hospital. The victims were cleaning the road near Ibrahimvas village when the incident occurred, leading to a major traffic disruption and a police investigation.
title: 7 dead, 4 critical as speeding van mows down group on Delhi-Mumbai Expressway

description: On Friday, Harshal Patel snared four wickets as Sunrisers Hyderabad defeated five-time champions Chennai Super Kings by five-wickets in a must-win game for the Pat Cummins-led side. With 13 wickets in eight games, Harshal has been the lone consistent performer for the hot-and-cold Sunrisers' outfit.
title: Harshal Patel: From working at a perfume store to disguising IPL batters

description: Apple is significantly increasing iPhone production in India, aiming for 70-80 million units by late 2026, potentially making India the primary supplier to the US. This shift, driven by diversification and geopolitical factors, could see India manufacturing nearly 40% of global iPhones.
title: In a shift away from China, 70-80 million iPhones to be made in India soon

description: Following Chennai Super Kings' continued struggles in IPL 2025, Ambati Rayudu suggests the team needs to adapt to modern T20 cricket. Despite some bright spots from Brevis and Mhatre, Rayudu believes significant squad changes are necessary for next season. He also anticipates an exciting clash between Shreyas Iyer's Punjab Kings and Kolkata Knight Riders, favoring Punjab as strong playoff contenders.
title: 'MS Dhoni is already thinking about ... ': CSK veteran drops bombshell

description: A Reddit post alleged that Zomato is losing market share, forcing employees to order from its platform, and fostering a toxic work environment. The post also highlighted issues with underpaid delivery partners and service outages. Zomato CEO Deepinder Goyal refuted these claims, dismissing them as "utter nonsense" and affirming the company's commitment to freedom of choice.
title: Zomato CEO Deepinder Goyal’s ‘embarrassing’ clarification on losing market share

description: India has suspended visa services for Pakistani nationals and revoked most existing visas, excluding long-term, diplomatic, and official ones, following a terror attack in Jammu and Kashmir. Pakistani nationals with SAARC, business, or medical visas must leave India by specific deadlines in late April.
title: 14 types of visas cancelled for Pak nationals: Who has to leave and by when?

description: Tahawwur Hussain Rana, a key figure in the 26/11 Mumbai attacks, is reportedly not cooperating with investigators, offering evasive answers during questioning. An Indian court denied Rana's request to speak with his family, citing concerns about potential information leaks.
title: 26/11 terror attack accused Rana not cooperating with investigation: Police

description: The Karnataka High Court has denied bail to actress Harshavardhini Ranya Rao and Tarun Konduru Raju, who are accused in a gold smuggling case. Ranya Rao was apprehended on March 3, 2025, with over 14 kg of gold concealed on her person. The Directorate of Revenue Intelligence (DRI) highlighted the duo's frequent travels to Dubai and presented evidence of the arrest memo being properly served.
title: Actor Ranya Rao bail plea rejected in gold smuggling case

description: Battling a restless mind? Cognitive shuffling, a playful mental exercise introduced by cognitive scientist Luc Beaudoin, offers a unique solution. No one wins against a racing mind by pushing harder. Sometimes, the most effective tools are the ones that might feel effortless. That’s what makes cognitive shuffling feel so magical.
title: Do you overthink a lot? Practice this technique to quiet racing thoughts

description: Seema Haider, who illegally entered India from Pakistan to marry Sachin Meena, fears deportation after India suspended visa services for Pakistani nationals following the Pahalgam terror attack. She appeals to PM Modi and UP CM Yogi to allow her to stay, claiming she is now India's daughter-in-law and has embraced Hinduism.
title: Don't want to go to Pakistan, I am India's daughter-in law now: Seema Haider

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack and India's suspension of the Indus Waters Treaty, Delhi minister Manjinder Singh Sirsa strongly criticized Pakistan's Bilawal Bhutto-Zardari's threats. Sirsa condemned Pakistan's support for terrorism and warned its officials against provocative actions, as protests erupted in London over the killings. The escalating tensions highlight the strained relationship between the two nations.
title: ‘Drown in it’: Delhi min's fiery retort to Bhutto's threat on Indus waters treaty

description: Eminent historian M G S Narayanan, former chairman of the Indian Council of Historical Research, passed away at his residence in Kozhikode at the age of 93. Renowned for his work on Kerala's socio-political history, particularly 'Perumals of Kerala,' he headed the history department at the University of Calicut and contributed significantly to Indian historiography.
title: Eminent historian M G S Narayanan passes away at 93 in Kerala

description: Chennai Super Kings (CSK) head coach Stephen Fleming has taken responsibility for the team's poor performance in the IPL 2025, admitting unsuccessful auction outcomes and urging players to improve. Highlighting injuries, form issues, and an unsettled strategy as key factors, Fleming acknowledged CSK's struggles after a five-wicket defeat to Sunrisers Hyderabad (SRH).
title: 'CSK got it wrong at the IPL auction': Fleming breaks silence

description: Yogeshwar Dutt has defended Neeraj Chopra after the javelin star faced social media abuse for inviting Pakistani athlete Arshad Nadeem to the NC Classic. Chopra clarified Nadeem's participation was impossible after the Pahalgam attack, emphasising his country's priority. Dutt lauded Chopra's patriotism and leadership, urging him to ignore critics and continue his success as a national champion.
title: 'Don't need to prove your patriotism': Yogeshwar Dutt to Neeraj

description: Following a deadly terrorist attack in Pahalgam and India's suspension of the Indus Waters Treaty, former Pakistani foreign minister Bilawal Bhutto-Zardari threatened India, asserting Pakistan's claim to the Indus River. Tensions have escalated, leading to internal discord in Pakistan over water projects and India initiating the repatriation of Pakistani nationals. Both nations are preparing for potential international disputes.
title: ‘Either water will flow or their blood will': Ex-Pak FM Bhutto's threat to India

description: Following the tragic Pahalgam terror attack on April 22, 2025, which claimed 26 innocent lives, the Federation of Western India Cine Employees (FWICE) has called for a complete ban on Pakistani artists working in India. Ashoke Dubey, General Secretary of FWICE, emphasized national interest and urged the government to charge Indian artists collaborating with Pakistani performers with treason.
title: FWICE demands blanket ban on Pakistani artistes; says 'Nation comes first'

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad defeated Chennai Super Kings at Chepauk, marking their first-ever win at the venue in IPL history and keeping their playoff hopes alive. CSK, on the other hand, suffered their joint-highest number of home defeats in a single season, dimming their chances of reaching the top four.
title: IPL 2025: After RCB, DC, CSK suffer another low at Chepauk against SRH

description: Chennai Super Kings' IPL 2025 playoff aspirations faced a significant setback after a five-wicket defeat to Sunrisers Hyderabad. This loss positions them at the bottom of the table with only four points from nine matches. While mathematically a playoff berth is still possible, CSK needs to win all remaining five games and rely on favourable outcomes from other matches.
title: IPL qualification scenarios: Can CSK reach the playoffs?

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad defeated Chennai Super Kings by five wickets, keeping their playoff hopes alive while virtually knocking CSK out of the tournament. SRH chased down CSK's 154-run target in 18.4 overs, marking their first-ever win at the MA Chidambaram Stadium. With the victory, SRH leapfrogged Rajasthan Royals to move into seventh place on the points table. Meanwhile, CSK, with just two wins from nine matches, are all but out of the tournament.
title: Kavya Maran's explosive reaction after Dhoni's genius tactic

description: Akshay Kumar's courtroom drama, 'Kesari Chapter 2: The Untold Story of Jallianwala Bagh,' has surpassed ₹50 crore in the domestic market after an eight-day theatrical run. The film saw a rise in collections on its second Friday, minting an estimated ₹4.15 crore. While 'Jaat' and 'Ground Zero' also released, they couldn't match 'Kesari 2's' Friday earnings.
title: ‘Kesari 2’ box office collection: Akshay starrer makes Rs 4cr more than ‘Jaat’

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, Donald Trump voiced concern over the India-Pakistan conflict, hoping for resolution. India retaliated by demolishing properties of suspected terrorists, while Pakistan threatened India over the Indus Waters Treaty suspension. In other news, MS Dhoni expressed frustration after a CSK loss, and Virginia Giuffre, known for her role in exposing Jeffrey Epstein, has died by suicide.
title: Morning news wrap: Trump addresses India-Pak tensions, terrorists' homes blown up & more

description: Mahendra Singh Dhoni expressed disappointment as Chennai Super Kings suffered a five-wicket defeat against Sunrisers Hyderabad, further diminishing their IPL 2025 play-off hopes. Dhoni felt that their score of 154 was inadequate on the Chepauk pitch, and the team's overall performance lacked cohesion. ​​CSK, meanwhile, sit at the bottom with just two wins from nine games and only four points to show.
title: MS Dhoni finally loses cool after CSK loss, says 'you can't just keep ... '

description: The 2025 NFL Draft captivated audiences, drawing 13.6 million viewers and marking the second-most watched opening round in its history, an 11% increase from 2024. Held in Green Bay with 205,000 fans in attendance, the draft embodies hope and possibility, uniting fans in anticipation of football's future stars and the promise of a fresh start for every team.
title: NFL draft first round pulls 13.6 million viewers
Pak official in UK seen making throat-slit gesture at Pahalgam attack protesters

description: A senior Russian general, Yaroslav Moskalik, was assassinated in a car bombing near Moscow, prompting accusations from Russia that Ukrainian special services were responsible. This marks the second such attack on high-ranking Russian military officials in recent months.
title: Video: Russian general Yaroslav Moskalik killed in car blast near Moscow
Video shows demolished homes of 5 terrorists days after Pahalgam terror attack

description: Virginia Giuffre, a prominent voice against Jeffrey Epstein's sex trafficking ring and accuser of Prince Andrew, has tragically died by suicide at 41. Her family confirmed her passing at their farm in Western Australia, citing lifelong sexual abuse and sex trafficking as contributing factors.
title: Virginia Giuffre, who accused Epstein & Prince Andrew of abuse, dies by suicide
WWE SmackDown highlights & results: TLC match steals the show and more
DGCA issues ‘mandatory guidance’ for Indian carriers amid airspace curbs

description: Gujarat authorities have detained over 550 undocumented Bangladeshi immigrants in a statewide crackdown, with significant operations in Surat and Ahmedabad. The raids, involving multiple police units, targeted individuals living with forged documents, who will be deported after investigation. This action aligns with a broader national effort, including a Delhi Police probe into illegal immigration networks, reflecting concerns over national security.
title: Major crackdown on immigrants in Gujarat: Over 500 Bangladeshi nationals detained

description: Amidst heightened tensions following the Pahalgam attack, Pakistan's Gull Feroza confirmed their women's cricket team will not play in India during the upcoming World Cup. Echoing PCB chairman Mohsin Naqvi's stance, Feroza stated a preference for Asian conditions, suggesting Sri Lanka or Dubai as potential neutral venues. Earlier this year, the Indian men's team also declined to travel to Pakistan for the Champions Trophy. As a result, their matches—including the final—were held in Dubai.
title: 'Not interested in playing in India': Pakistan cricketer sparks controversy

description: World leaders and dignitaries have converged on St. Peter's Square to honor Pope Francis, who passed away at 88 from heart failure. The funeral ceremony, attended by figures like Donald Trump, Emmanuel Macron, and President Murmu of India, marks a significant moment of global mourning. Notable absences include Vladimir Putin and Benjamin Netanyahu due to international arrest warrants.
title: President Murmu, Trump, Zelenskyy: List of world leaders attending Pope's funeral

description: The United Nations Security Council strongly condemned the recent terrorist attack in Jammu and Kashmir on April 22, which resulted in at least 26 fatalities and numerous injuries. The Council emphasized the urgent need to hold the perpetrators, organizers, and financiers of this reprehensible act accountable and bring them to justice.
title: 'Reprehensible act of terrorism': UNSC strongly condemns Pahalgam attack

description: The Rashtriya Janata Dal (RJD) has criticized Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Bihar Chief Minister Nitish Kumar for holding a political rally in Bihar while the nation mourns the victims of the Pahalgam terror attack. RJD alleges the state administration pressured officials to ensure crowd attendance.
title: RJD poster targets PM Modi, Nitish for Bihar rally days after J&K attack

description: President Trump admitted he was too occupied to purchase a birthday gift for First Lady Melania Trump, who turned 55 on Saturday. Instead, he planned a dinner aboard Air Force One as they returned from Pope Francis’s funeral in Rome.
title: What 'busy' Donald Trump did for wife Melania Trump on her birthday

description: Maruti Suzuki is slowing down land acquisition for its second Gujarat factory, a Rs 35,000-crore project, due to sluggish car sales growth. Chairman R C Bhargava stated that current expansion plans in Haryana and Gujarat are sufficient, given the market's 1-2% growth.
title: Maruti goes slow on new plant amid sluggish sales

description: Sunny Deol and Randeep Hooda's action drama 'Jaat,' released on April 10, 2025, has grossed Rs 81.6 crore after a 16-day theatrical run. While the film initially performed well, its box office collection has slowed down, earning only Rs 85 lakh on its third Friday. 'Jaat' also faced competition from 'Kesari Chapter 2' and the newly released 'Ground Zero'.
title: ‘Jaat’ Box Office collection: Sunny Deol-starrer records its lowest on third Friday

description: Following the murder of restaurant worker Gulfam Ali in Agra, Manoj Chaudhary, claiming affiliation with 'Kshatriya Gau Raksha Dal,' asserted responsibility, citing it as retaliation for the Pahalgam attack. He threatened further violence in a widely circulated video. However, Agra police dismissed the claims, labeling it a publicity stunt, and attributed the crime to a prior dispute over food quality.
title: Biryani seller shot; 'Pahalgam avenged': Killer

description: In Chennai, a teenage girl was attacked with a blade by two men near Washermenpet on Thursday night. The assault was retaliation for her sexual assault complaint against their 35-year-old brother, which led to his arrest.
title: Sexual assault: Minor files plaint, 2 men slashed her with blade in Chennai

description: A World Bank report reveals India's significant progress in poverty reduction, with extreme poverty plummeting from 16.2% in 2011-12 to 2.3% in 2022-23, lifting 171 million people out of extreme poverty. The rural-urban gap has narrowed, and India has transitioned into the lower-middle-income category.
title: 171 million lifted above poverty line in 10 yrs: World Bank

description: Ahead of Mamata Banerjee's visit to Murshidabad and Jangipur, the West Bengal government has transferred the police superintendents of both districts. Ananda Roy, involved in the Murshidabad violence SIT, is moved to West Midnapore, while Surya Kumar Yadav, part of the probe team, is transferred to Cooch Behar.
title: 2 SPs shifted days after Bengal violence

description: The Union government informed the Supreme Court that a 2013 amendment to the Waqf Act, which removed the bar on enforcing rights over unregistered waqfs, led to a significant increase in Waqf Board properties nationwide. Properties surged from 2,07,394 to 8,72,870, and the area expanded from 18.
title: Delhi waqf board properties rose from 9 to 1,047 in 12 yrs
NEET-UG paper leak mastermind held

description: The Supreme Court has mandated a fresh investigation into the 2022 death of Ziaul Rahman, overturning previous court orders that applied a lesser charge. Citing the autopsy report detailing 14 injuries, the SC has directed that murder charges be framed. The court has given Uttar Pradesh six weeks to complete the trial and appoint a special prosecutor.
title: Probe killing of man in interfaith romance: Supreme Court

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, US President Trump acknowledged the long-standing India-Pakistan tensions, expressing hope for resolution. India responded with diplomatic measures, including suspending the SAARC Visa Exemption Scheme and halting Indus Waters Treaty participation. These actions followed the deadly strike where 25 Indian tourists and one Nepali citizen were killed, escalating already strained relations between the two nations.
title: 'That was a bad one': Trump reacts to Pahalgam terror attack
